Data Cleaning & Preparation
Several preprocessing and transformation steps were performed before dashboard development.
Cleaning Activities
•	Standardized column formats
•	Validated date fields
•	Checked for duplicate records
•	Ensured consistency across datasets
•	Formatted pricing and sales metrics
•	Structured relational data using lookup functions
Data Modeling
•	Linked orders, customers, and products datasets
•	Created calculated metrics for sales reporting
•	Built pivot-based reporting tables
•	Enabled interactive filtering through slicers
________________________________________
Key Insights
Sales Insights
•	Certain coffee types generate significantly higher revenue than others.
•	Sales performance varies across countries and customer segments.
•	Repeat customers contribute substantially to total revenue.
Customer Insights
•	Loyalty card holders tend to generate higher purchase value.
•	A small group of customers contributes disproportionately to overall sales.
•	Geographic customer distribution highlights strong regional markets.
Product Insights
•	Specific roast types perform better in certain regions.
•	Premium products contribute higher profitability despite lower volume.
•	Product size influences purchasing patterns and average order value.
